# vMCP - Virtual Model Context Protocol

An open-source tool for aggregating and managing multiple MCP servers with a unified interface.


vMCP (Virtual Model Context Protocol) is an open-source platform that allows you to connect to different mcp servers, modify them and add new tools, prompts . vMCP allows user to create customised mcp servers that can be used as drop in replactement in the agent building platforms. 

### Highlight Features

- âœ… **Flexible Proxy Server Creation**: Selectively combine different MCP servers into a unified proxy server.
- ğŸ› ï¸ **Customizable Tools**: Override tool names/descriptions and prefill tool arguments.
- âœ¨ **Extensible Tooling**: Create new tools using Python snippets or REST APIs or plain text. 
- ğŸ—£ï¸ **Programmable Prompts**: Define prompts that can invoke other tools, enabling user-controlled tool chaining.
- ğŸ” **MCP Server Authentication**: OAuth 2.0 support for MCP servers that require it
- ğŸ“Š **Usage Statistics**: Track and analyze vMCP usage patterns
- ğŸ³ **Docker Ready**: Official Docker images for easy deployment
- ğŸ“ **Standard Logging**: Clean logging with DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR levels

<div align="center">
  <img src=".assets/img/vmcp-arch.png" alt="vMCP Architecture" width="780"/>
</div>

## ğŸš€ Quickstart

### Prerequisites

vMCP requires [Python 3.10 to 3.13](https://www.python.org/downloads/) and [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/).

### Installation

To install vMCP, run:

#### Option 1: Using uvx (Recommended)
```bash
uvx --with 1xn-vmcp vmcp run
```
Or using uv

#### Option 2: Using pip
```bash
pip install 1xn-vmcp
vmcp run
```

#### Option 3: Using Docker
```bash
docker pull onexn/vmcp:latest
docker run -it onexn/vmcp:latest vmcp run
```
```

##docker deployement :


This will start the vMCP server on `http://localhost:8000`.

